  m_Name: Navigation History
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Trailback.Demo.Features.Data.FeatureDemoData
  featureName: Navigation History
  shortDescription: Automatically track navigation state and return to previous UI
    elements.
  fullDescription: 'Trailback automatically maintains navigation history as users
    move through your UI.


    Instead of creating and managing your own back stack,
    Trailback keeps track of navigation state for screens, popups, overlays, and
    other navigable elements. This allows applications to return to previously visited
    UI without additional history management code.


    Features include:


    *
    Automatic History Tracking

    * Back Navigation Support

    * Category-Aware
    Navigation

    * Navigation State Management


    Whether you''re building
    a simple menu flow or a more complex layered UI, Trailback helps keep navigation
    history organized and back navigation behavior consistent.'
